---
description: Product delivery standards for features, experiments, and UX work
alwaysApply: true
---

- Preserve product intent: user problem, scope, acceptance criteria, and out-of-scope.
- For UI work, include empty/loading/error/success/permission-denied states.
- For risky product changes, prefer flags and staged rollout.
- For experiments, define hypothesis, primary metric, guardrails, and stop conditions.
- Every user-visible change should consider analytics and logging requirements.
- If a change materially alters behavior, update docs/prd and link the changed decision.
